Klopp: &ldquo;We know about this situation. There are no more points to waste.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Klopp: &ldquo;If we win the next three games then we&rsquo;re through. The next game after tonight is away in Sevilla - not the easiest place to go.&rdquo;

Klopp: &ldquo;For all our young boys, it&rsquo;s not about what they do now, it&rsquo;s about what they keep doing. Rhian is on a great road.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Klopp: &ldquo;But it is just the beginning. Our job is to give them time, protection and freedom to embrace the joy that comes ar their age.&rdquo;

Klopp: &ldquo;On Saturday night I kept watching clips back from the England U17s World Cup final win and even more clips of them celebrating.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Klopp: &ldquo;What a great moment for Rhian, his family and his team-mates. Alex Inglethorpe, our outstanding Academy leader.&rdquo;

Klopp: &quot;We knew what we had to do in the second half, it was a similar situation to Huddersfield, but an even more defensive side.&quot;<br />
<br />
Klopp: &quot;We did the same things wrong, wrong positions, not enough offers in behind, we didn't create enough, it was hard work.&quot;
